        "last_activity_date": 1394304694,
        "creation_date": 1394304694,
        "body": "<p>To trigger something, use a <a href=\"http://www.sqlite.org/lang_createtrigger.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">trigger<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<p>SQLite has no built-in mechanism to detect the byte size of a table; the best you could do is to count records:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"lang-sql prettyprint-override\"><code>CREATE TRIGGER WipeOnOverflow\nAFTER INSERT ON MyTable\nWHEN (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM MyTable) &gt; 1000\nBEGIN\n    DELETE FROM MyTable;\nEND;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>or:<\/p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-sql prettyprint-override\"><code>CREATE TRIGGER DeleteOneRecordOnOverflow\nAFTER INSERT ON MyTable\nFOR EACH ROW\nWHEN (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM MyTable) &gt; 1000\nBEGIN\n    DELETE FROM MyTable WHERE rowid = (SELECT MIN(rowid) FROM MyTable);\nEND;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "answer_id": 22273585,
        "question_id": 22261830
    }],
